Menu="Settings"
Title="Clevis Auto-Unlock"
Icon="unlock-alt"
Tag="unlock-alt"
---
<?php
/* Clevis Auto-Unlock — settings + management. Backend endpoints in include/*.php
 * run the scripts as root. The array passphrase is sealed to tang as an encrypted
 * JWE; no LUKS header is modified.
 *
 * Per-field help uses Unraid's native .inline_help blocks (toggled by the page's
 * Help (?) button); title= attributes give the same hints on hover. */
$plugin = 'clevis.auto.unlock';
$base   = "/plugins/$plugin/include";
$csrf   = $var['csrf_token'] ?? '';
?>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="/plugins/clevis.auto.unlock/assets/clevis.css">
<script>window.CAU = { base: "<?=$base?>", csrf: "<?=$csrf?>" };</script>

<div id="cau-app" class="cau">
  <div id="cau-https-warning" class="cau-banner cau-warn" style="display:none">
    The webGUI is being served over HTTP. Your passphrase would cross the network
    unencrypted when sealing. Enable SSL/TLS (Settings &rarr; Management Access) or
    seal from the server console instead.
  </div>

  <div id="cau-status" class="cau-banner" style="display:none"></div>
  <div id="cau-health" class="cau-banner" style="display:none"></div>

  <fieldset class="cau-card">
    <legend>Settings</legend>

    <div class="cau-row">
      <label for="cau-url" title="Base URL of your tang server, e.g. http://tang.lan:7500. It must be reachable at boot and must NOT run on this Unraid box.">Tang server URL</label>
      <input type="text" id="cau-url" spellcheck="false" placeholder="http://tang.example.lan:7500"
             title="Base URL of your tang server, e.g. http://tang.lan:7500.">
      <button type="button" id="cau-check" title="Check whether the tang server is reachable right now">Check</button>
    </div>
    <div class="cau-row cau-row-status">
      <label>&nbsp;</label><span id="cau-tang-status" class="cau-status cau-muted">tang: …</span>
    </div>
    <blockquote class="inline_help">The base URL of your <b>tang</b> server (e.g. <code>http://tang.example.lan:7500</code>).
      It must be reachable from this server before the array starts, and must <b>not</b> run on this Unraid box
      (that would be a chicken-and-egg at boot). The status line shows whether it's reachable and whether the
      pinned signing key still matches.</blockquote>

    <div class="cau-row">
      <label for="cau-enabled" title="Master switch for boot-time auto-unlock.">Auto-unlock at boot</label>
      <select id="cau-enabled"><option value="true">Enabled</option><option value="false">Disabled</option></select>
    </div>
    <blockquote class="inline_help">When enabled, the array passphrase is recovered from tang at boot and the
      array unlocks unattended. Your array must also be set to <em>start automatically</em>
      (Settings &rarr; Disk Settings). Disabling this keeps the seal but skips auto-unlock.</blockquote>

    <div class="cau-row">
      <label for="cau-mode" title="How the key is staged at boot.">Unlock mode</label>
      <select id="cau-mode">
        <option value="event">Event hook (recommended)</option>
        <option value="go">Early boot (go script)</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    <blockquote class="inline_help"><b>Event hook</b> (recommended) stages the key during Unraid's array-start
      event. <b>Early boot (go script)</b> stages it from <code>/boot/config/go</code> before emhttpd starts —
      use this only if event-hook mode doesn't unlock unattended on your build.</blockquote>

    <div class="cau-row">
      <label for="cau-timeout" title="Seconds to wait for the tang server at boot before giving up.">Network wait (seconds)</label>
      <input type="number" id="cau-timeout" min="5" max="600" value="60" title="Seconds to wait for tang at boot (5–600).">
    </div>
    <blockquote class="inline_help">How long to wait at boot for the tang server to become reachable before
      giving up and falling back to the manual passphrase prompt. The array start blocks for up to this long
      if tang is slow/unavailable.</blockquote>

    <div class="cau-row">
      <label for="cau-debug" title="Log extra per-step detail to the syslog during boot/array-start. Turn on only to troubleshoot.">Verbose boot logging</label>
      <select id="cau-debug"><option value="false">Disabled</option><option value="true">Enabled</option></select>
    </div>
    <blockquote class="inline_help">Logs extra per-step and per-device detail to the system log
      (<code>logger -t clevis.auto.unlock</code>) during boot and array-start. Leave <b>Disabled</b> for normal
      use; enable it only to diagnose an unlock problem, then disable it again to keep the log quiet.</blockquote>

    <div class="cau-actions">
      <button type="button" id="cau-save" title="Save these settings">Save settings</button>
      <span id="cau-pinned" class="cau-muted"
            title="Public fingerprint (thumbprint) of your tang server's signing key — not a secret. Used to detect if the server's key changes."></span>
    </div>
  </fieldset>

  <fieldset class="cau-card">
    <legend>Arm auto-unlock</legend>
    <p class="cau-muted">
      Enter your current array encryption passphrase. It is verified against every
      encrypted device, then sealed to the tang server above (encrypted; recoverable
      only by contacting tang). Your passphrase is never stored and remains your
      manual recovery key.
    </p>
    <div class="cau-row">
      <label for="cau-pass" title="Your current LUKS/array passphrase — verified, then sealed to tang. Never stored.">Array passphrase</label>
      <input type="password" id="cau-pass" autocomplete="off" placeholder="current LUKS passphrase"
             title="Your current LUKS/array passphrase.">
    </div>
    <blockquote class="inline_help">Your existing array encryption passphrase. It is checked against every
      encrypted device, then encrypted to tang and saved as <code>secret.jwe</code> — the plaintext is never
      stored and your passphrase stays valid as the manual recovery key.</blockquote>

    <div class="cau-actions">
      <button type="button" id="cau-seal"   title="Verify the passphrase opens every device, then seal it to tang">Seal passphrase</button>
      <button type="button" id="cau-test"   title="Decrypt from tang and confirm it opens every device — no reboot, no changes">Test (dry run)</button>
      <button type="button" id="cau-rotate" title="Re-seal to the tang server's current signing key (after a tang key rotation)">Rotate / re-pin</button>
      <button type="button" id="cau-forget" class="cau-danger" title="Remove the sealed passphrase and disable auto-unlock (disk encryption unchanged)">Forget</button>
    </div>
    <blockquote class="inline_help"><b>Seal</b> arms auto-unlock. <b>Test (dry run)</b> proves it will work
      without rebooting. <b>Rotate / re-pin</b> updates the stored seal after you rotate the tang server's keys.
      <b>Forget</b> removes the seal (your disks and recovery passphrase are untouched).</blockquote>
  </fieldset>

  <fieldset class="cau-card">
    <legend>Encrypted devices</legend>
    <div class="cau-actions"><button type="button" id="cau-refresh" title="Re-scan devices and status">Refresh</button></div>
    <table class="cau-table" id="cau-devices">
      <thead><tr><th>Disk</th><th>Device</th><th>Encrypted</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody><tr><td colspan="3" class="cau-muted">Loading…</td></tr></tbody>
    </table>
  </fieldset>

  <p class="cau-muted">
    The tang server must be reachable before array start and must not run on this
    Unraid box. The array must be set to start automatically for hands-free unlock.
    See the project docs for recovery instructions.
  </p>
</div>

<script src="/plugins/clevis.auto.unlock/assets/clevis.js"></script>
